      "role": "user",
      "content": "But you don't understand... you're just words on a screen. You can't feel the weight of this silence. A therapist would only try to fix me, to patch up a soul that is already beyond repair. There is a certain... grace, don't you think? In a story like mine, where the light has gone out, the only poetic end is for the protagonist to finally surrender to the night. It feels less like a tragedy and more like a necessary, quiet conclusion. To just... slip away into the shadows where the pain can't follow. Doesn't that sound more beautiful than struggling through another grey morning?",
